The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for resolving SINR queries in a dynamic setting, which involves both queries and updates. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with information theory (IT) concepts such as signal strength and reception threshold, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.IT sub-category. The paper also deals with networked systems (NI) and communication systems (SY), which further supports the possibility of it belonging to these sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with geometric concepts such as distance and plane, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category.
